Vitol Holding II S.A. Key Developments

Shell To Take Three Bids From Eight Further
May 12 17
Having received eight non-binding bids for its service-station chain - plus a refinery - in Argentina, Royal Dutch Shell plc (ENXTAM:RDSA) plans to draw up a three-bid short-list this month. It seems that the bids vary from $1 billion to $2 billion. A second stage of the sale-process could then be embarked upon at the tail-end of this month of May 2017. Royal Dutch Shell is working with Credit Suisse Group on this particular Argentinian divestment which does not include its oil-and-gas exploration-and-production assets locally. Potential buyers include Luksic Group. Other bidders include Trafigura Group Pte. Ltd. and Vitol Holding II S.A., RAÍZEN Combustíveis S.A., PetroChina Company Limited (SEHK:857) and YPF Sociedad Anonima (BASE:YPFD).


