Vitol Holding B.V.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg










































  





















































































July 29, 2017 12:47 AM ET
Oil, Gas and Consumable Fuels

Company Overview of Vitol Holding B.V.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Vitol Holding B.V., an energy and commodities company, engages in trading, refining, shipping, terminals and storage, exploration and production, marketing, and power generation businesses. It trades crude oil, fuel oil, gasoline, middle distillates, naphtha, methanol, ethanol, chemicals, LPG, natural gas, LNG, power, coal, iron ore, alumina, carbon emissions, base oils, and bitumen; owns and operates refineries that distil crude oil into fuels, such as gasoline, diesel, jet fuel and bunker oil, and raw materials; and owns and charters ships to deliver crude oil and oil products, as well as coal, bitumen, chemicals, and pressurized gas. The company also engages in the distribution of finishe...
Vitol Holding B.V., an energy and commodities company, engages in trading, refining, shipping, terminals and storage, exploration and production, marketing, and power generation businesses. It trades crude oil, fuel oil, gasoline, middle distillates, naphtha, methanol, ethanol, chemicals, LPG, natural gas, LNG, power, coal, iron ore, alumina, carbon emissions, base oils, and bitumen; owns and operates refineries that distil crude oil into fuels, such as gasoline, diesel, jet fuel and bunker oil, and raw materials; and owns and charters ships to deliver crude oil and oil products, as well as coal, bitumen, chemicals, and pressurized gas. The company also engages in the distribution of finished products to wholesale partners and end-consumers; supplies bunker fuel for ships and jet fuel to airlines. Vitol Holding B.V. was founded in 1966 and is based in Rotterdam, the Netherlands with additional offices worldwide. It has operations in Geneva, Houston, London, Moscow, Rotterdam, and Singapore. Vitol Holding B.V. operates as a subsidiary of Vitol Holding II S.A.
