Vitol Holding B.V. Key Developments

Hascol Petroleum Limited Forms Joint Venture With Vitol Group
Mar 16 17
Hascol Petroleum Limited formed joint venture with Vitol Group to explore the business opportunities in the LNG sector. The joint venture company is named as VAS LNG (Private) Limited. Vitol owns 70% stake and Hascol Petroleum owns the remaining 30% stake in the VAS LNG. The transaction enables Hascol Petroleum to expand its LNG business.


Vitol, China Petroleum & Chemical Reportedly Final Bidders For Chevron South Africa Sale
Dec 15 16
Vitol Holding B.V. and China Petroleum & Chemical Corporation (SEHK:386) are reportedly two final bidders competing to buy Chevron Corporation (NYSE:CVX)'s South African assets. Vitol Group and China Petroleum & Chemical Corp, known as Sinopec, are the two final bidders competing to buy Chevron Corp's South African assets, which could be worth about $1 billion, according to people familiar with the matter. TOTAL S.A. (ENXTPA:FP) and Gunvor Group Ltd have dropped out of the bidding, the people said, asking not to be identified as the information is private. Chevron plans to make a decision on the winner in the coming weeks, though the sale talks could still falter, the people said. The sale may fetch about $1 billion, people familiar with the matter said in March, 2016. "The process initiated by Chevron Global Energy Inc. to solicit expressions of interest for its 75% shareholding of Chevron South Africa (Pty) Limited is ongoing," Braden Reddall, a Chevron spokesman, said. Andrea Schlaepfer, a spokeswoman for Vitol declined to comment on the matter. Total and Gunvor Group also declined to comment. A representative of Sinopec, declined to comment.


Companies Interested To Acquire Stake In Petrobras Distribution Business
Oct 4 16
Itausa - Investimentos Itau S.A. (BOVESPA:ITSA4), Cambuhy Investimentos Ltda., Vitol Holding B.V., Advent International Corporation, GP Investimentos S.A are reportedly planning to acquire a controlling stake in Petrobras Distribuidora S.A. from  Petroleo Brasileiro S.A. - Petrobas (BOVESPA:PETR4). The Setubal and Vilella families’ Itausa - Investimentos Itau SA and the Moreira Salles family’s Cambuhy Investimentos Ltda. are planning to make a joint bid for a controlling stake in Petrobras’s BR Distribuidora in a deal that could reach $6 billion, the people said, asking not to be identified because the discussions are private. 


